	   <tr><td colspan=2>concordance research is good. Many say it's a waste of time but it also allows you to make friends easy, this is how: alot of times you will need a group to get these items. The items themselves are worthless to most except to sell, like giant snake rattles, or undead froglock tongues, or griffon feathers. since you loot these and the occacional piece of armor, oyu are not known as a loot hog. Also, these items take you to places where other good things can be gotten, like a sewn evil eye bag-in lower guk that you can roll for while getting undead tongues. also, going to the ro deserts for components gives you a better chance of seeing the ancient cyclops, random trips, random spawn-maybe he will be there when you need your giant scarab eyes. It trains you to manage space, only 3 out of the 10 items needed for both runes are stackable, and it adds to character if people see you dropping parchement to make room, but once you make your runes if you can in battle, you have more room to carry things. The other plus, having this room and getting used to keeping space really helps to manage the terrortantula silk. good prices if not erudite, great to hold if erudite-erudite cultural armor is quite nice, and can be traded to humans, maybe that human wizard for ports, and the making uses some research elements you need for other spells. 9 out of 10 if others see you only going for the paltry item, you will get to loot the one item that will fetch you plat, or the group will allow you to get the nice weight reduction bag, sometimes. good place to solo 36 to 40? dreadlands yeti caves. plenty of time to med and they do not get aggravated unless you are very close, other plus? frosty daturas that can be traded to rogues for their higher level poison, yes they can be sold for 1p and change per flower, but the trade for white lead or celestial <br>essences or velium tempers is valuable for other pottery things. Concordance give you the need to go to places that have interesting spells, like the merchant in north ro tunnel, or rathmana's game in south ro. also keep your necromancer words if you find them to trade with other necromancers, they can shop in the smugglers areas, and find components for cheap! for instance, gloves of rollos zek in smugglers den went for less than 5 gold, words of bondage, 2plat and change, only two available, but, worth it. Trade a few words, and have the necro shop for you, not bad all around. Rathmana's game makes for nice spells to trade to younger players, so that they may keep the ringmail for you that they loot, rather than sell, saves the 20 plat to pay for ringmail in highpass. Notice that for journey to master condordance runes, you are always drawn to the ro desserts, if not also to get to lower guk which has good loot. the undead also drop gems, there pearls-master runes, and raw-hide-journey runes. The more times you need to head there, the more chances you have of meeting the ancient cyclops, and finding groups. Fastest way to level from 16 to 24 is in paludal, and in a group. I went from 16 to 20 in four hours with a full group, then 20 to 24 the next two evenings with full groups at camp 2 in paludal.At 29, you can solo the gnolls outside split paw in south karana with earth pet, if you want to build melee skills and no groups are around. BTW groups will want mages since you can target elemental to the add, have elemental take beating while you seperately help with the other two adds, nice to see elemental perish when the other three beasts are gone, everyone at 50 health, and one remaining beast left, you have 40 mana, beast is at 80 health, can-do with group and plenty of time to med afterwards. elemental will take aggravation away from one of the two beasts beating up your tank as well.<img src=/ubbnew/graemlins/smile.gif><br>&nbsp;<br>Manouk, Magician, Firiona Vie</td></tr>
