	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's the rundown on the effects and percentages of summoned focus items:<br><br>1. Earring - reduces mana usage by 15% for &quot;damaging&quot; spells. i.e. malosini, nukes, etc.<br><br>2. Shawl - increases durations of buffs that you cast by 15%<br><br>3. Ring - reduces casting time of spells that you cast by 20%.&nbsp;&nbsp;The exceptions are spells under 2.0 seconds and &gt;9.5 seconds, which it doesn't effect at all.<br><br>4. Bracelet - increases nuke damage by 20%<br><br>5. Necklace - gives a 15% chance of not using a reagent when casting a spell.<br><br>Note that NO FOCUS ITEM REDUCES AGRO!  This is a MISTAKE by castersrealm that they have refused to fix, even in the face of dozens of emails from myself and other mages.  Other sites just pass on the bad information.<br>&nbsp;<br>--<br>Jeroo Ashstaff</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
