<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=10302050332272></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10302050332272><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=10302050332272>Soloing</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=10302050332272#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=182028><span id= >Rolstin</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 24th 12:16 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are many posts asking where to hunt for a specific level range.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have soloed my mage from 1 to 53 with no problems.<br><br>I play an Erudite mage.  If you are all about the stats, no other race makes sense for a mage.  If you are about roll playing, any race will do.  That's why they make magical gear.  You can max out int with any of the available races.<br><br>Very few people- more likely no people- are true noobs.  I was a true noob mage, and money was tight until about L20.  Since you are more than likely making an alt, arrange to transfer just 100 plat or so, and your new mage will never have to worry about buying spells or malachite.<br><br>OK.  This is not the only way to go, but it certainly works.<br><br>L1-5:  Paineel noob area is great and empty.  You'll ding 5 in no time. <br>L6-10:  Head to Misty.  Hopefully, you can get a port there.  I managed it with no effort.<br><br>on a PL note, if you have a Druid in your pocket, you can go from L1 to L10 in about an hour.  With SLD and a damage shield, you won't need a pet at all for 10 levels.  Mobs will run up to you and die, but we all know this already....<br><br>L11-12or13:  Go to North Ro.  You won't be here long.  Giant scarabs, desert tarants, madmen... be careful of derv camps if you are still soloing.  and note that guards will not protect you from madmen.<br><br>L14-17 or 18:  Slide down to the Oasis.  Caimans first, then go tougher.  Crocs, DW Caimnans, then DW Crocs.  Rotten loot but good exp.  You'll see the occasional ghoul a bit inland for some loot.  You could stay here longer, but it tends to be over populated.<br><br>19-29:  Everfrost and/or SK:  mammoth tusks are the first decent money i started to get.  fill up your dimensional pockets with tusks...  and SK: the aviaks and the centaurs.  there are several levels of each, so you can always fight in your weight class.  the top of the line mobs, aviak avocets and centaur chargers are approx L25, so you can stay in SK for quite a while.<br><br>L30-36:  Iceclad.  there is an icegnoll shaman.  park it by him and pull snow cougars.  it is dull.  you'll get some cougar claw earrings which actually have decent stats.  oh what they sold for back in the day....<br><br>L37-44:  GD for the cave kodiaks.  terrible loot.  MAD exp.  three types...  ferals are the weakest, savages are midrange, and ferocious are pretty tough.  watch out for Icetooth, named cave kodiak.  Soloable at 44.  if you try him earlier, have SoW as a buff you'll probably need it.<br><br>L45-48:  GD for the frost giants.  stay near EW zone.  again, a safe spot for soloing.  decent loot.  while you're killing these things, farm toes and Kromrif heads.  4 toes will do part one of the Coldain prayer shawl quest.  10 heads will do the second.  then, sell your leftovers in thurg.  someone is usually starting the quest, and parts one and two, you can buy.<br><br>L49-53:  OOT.  once you have a 49 earthpet, the seafury cykes are your best friends.  solo.  in my experience, there is a huge penalty for having a partner.  and finally, a bit of money.  they tend to drop 4-6 plat each.  plus, they drop mithril amulets, fire emeralds, opal bracelets, etc.  items worth 50-100plat each.<br><br>for some variety, sneak into the third gate of neriak, and kill the triple spawn of 2 X'Lottls and one guard.  works from 51-52.  <br><br>also, check out Cyndreela.  she's a L40 necro that guards the Fear portal in Feerrott.  She's a 6 minute static spawn that is a cakewalk.  At 49, she's easy.  probably doable before then, but you have to be able to clear out the spectre caves to get to her.<br><br>i'm not sure what i'll do at 55, though... tba<br>&nbsp;<br>Rolstin<br><br>either solo, or get in a group of one.</td></tr>
