	   <tr><td colspan=2>Let ya in on a secret. No one seems to have trouble with the practice research aspect because no one does practice research. You're much better off finding some poor SoB who went through all the work (like me) to get research up and have HIM do the combine.<br><br>Mage research is extremely annoying. With the addition of the Katta Castellum tower spell vendors, research, mage research in particular, is no longer really necessiary. Those who did it in the first place usually just maxed it out with practice points.<br><br>That's what I did. Every level I used my trainer points to max out research. And yeah. It got expensive. The last 50 points cost over 2000pp.<br><br>But I'll tell ya this. It beats farming greens for months.<br><br>At this point with the KC tower selling research spells, you're a lot better off just having a high level mage research the ones the tower doesn't sell for you. It'll save you a huge headache.<br><br>However, to answer your question, the quills and parchments are on vendors inside most caster guilds. You can buy em from the same people you buy elemental binders from. Try the waters edge of the mage guild section in Kethelen. (ok I can't spell my home city. sue me.)<br><br>Oh, and if you MUST do this the hard way, I'd highly suggest binding at the firepots in T-Deep. I've gotten a level 15 over there with no trouble. But they have added KoS fishies since then... <br><br>The Firepot room is an underwater room at the far southwest corner of tdeep. it has 12 torches and by clicking on them you can get ports to almost anywhere in norrath and kunark except for qeynos. Should save on boatrides. Good luck.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Aug 21 15:18:07 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
