	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are helping your pet by meleeing your target, make sure you don't accidentally target your pet. Not sure if rules change from server to server, but pretty sure if your pet receives any damage from you, either melee or non, it has the same effect as pet get lost. Also, just noticed that you were using Flame bolt, which is a line of sight spell. If your pet is engaged in melee, and happens to step in front of you when you cast, it just screams and disappears. My recommendation is that you take pet sensitivity training. Of course, there are different techniques depending on which pet. I find that with earth pets, it takes a considerable amount of yelling and cursing and overall frustration to get through their heads what it is that you want them to do. Repeated beatings though will cause them to eventually turn on you from what I hear. Air pets need to be cajoled and understood and listened to, or they will just break down and disappear. Too much work if you ask me. By the way, do you know what 1,000 battered pets have in common? ...................They just won't listen.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Aug 21 12:27:54 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
